  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, ginger, cumin, coriander, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the lamb cubes to the bowl and toss to coat with the marinade.",
    "Thread the lamb cubes onto skewers, leaving a small space between each cube.",
    "Place the skewers in individual mini cocottes.",
    "Top each skewer with a slice of persian cucumber.",
    "Bake the kebabs in the preheated oven for 20 minutes, or until cooked through and crispy on the outside.",
    "Serve the kebabs hot, garnished with additional cucumber slices if desired."
